{"cursor":"4973","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox musical artist \n| name = Markus Dravs image = caption = image_size = background =\n| non_performing_personnel birth_date = death_date = origin = genre = occupation\n| = Producer, engineer, audio mixer years_active =\n| 1992âPresent label = associated_acts = website = http://www.markusdravs.com/\n| current_members = past_members = notable_instruments =\n}}\n\n'Markus Dravs' is a music producer, programmer, engineer, and mixer.\n\nAfter hearing Brian Eno's collaboration with David Byrne [[My Life in the Bush\nof Ghosts (album)|My Life in the Bush of Ghosts]], he decided to get into\nengineering.\n\nHe started out at Westside/Hookend Manor and learnt his initial skills from the\nthen owners, Clive Langer and Allan Winstanley, before moving to Metropolis,\nwhere he assisted under Gary Langan, before working under Brian Eno for the next\nfew years. He went on to get his first co-production credit on Eno's album\n[[Nerve Net]] in 1992 and they subsequently worked together on many productions\nincluding 12\" remixes for Depeche Mode, The Grid, and 808 State.\n\nHe has worked on several notable albums, including James's [[Wah Wah]], BjÃ¶rk's\n[[Homogenic]], and Arcade Fire's albums [[Neon Bible]] and [[The Suburbs\n(album)|The Suburbs]].\n\nHe has also worked with Coldplay on their 2008 album [[Viva la Vida or Death and\nAll His Friends]]. According to Markus: \"Chris Martin called me and told me he\nhad a conversation with Win Butler, who suggested, 'Heâll kick you into shape'\nwhich was poetic for 'He will do his utmost in helping you to develop your\nartistic horizon.'\"\n\nIn 2011 Dravs received acclaim for producing Mumford & Sons' debut album, [[Sigh\nNo More (Mumford & Sons album)|Sigh No More]], and Arcade Fire's [[The Suburbs\n(album)|The Suburbs]]. Sigh No More won Best British Album, and The Suburbs won\nBest International Album, at the 2011 BRIT Awards. The Suburbs also won the\nGrammy for Album of the Year.\n\nDravs also received praise for producing Coldplay's fifth studio album, [[Mylo\nXyloto]] (Parlophone Records/EMI), which was released 21 October 2011 via\nParlophone Records/EMI. This album has been nominated for Best Rock Album at the\n55th annual session of the '[[Grammy Award]]s' in 2013.\n\nDravs produced Mumford & Sons' second album, [[Babel (album)|Babel]], which was\nreleased 25 September 2012. This album was nominated for Best Americana Album at\nthe 55th annual session of the '[[Grammy Award]]s' in 2013 and won Album of the Year during the same ceremony.\n\nDravs himself was also nominated for Producer of the Year, Non-Classical at the\n55th annual session of the '[[Grammy Award]]s' in 2013.\n\nIn conjunction with Kobalt Music Group, Dravs has started up a publishing and\nproduction company called Casa-D. According to Markus \"The idea behind Casa-D\nProductions is to form a creative hub, from which I can collaborate with other\nmusicians, top line writers and lyricists to write and/or produce new songs both\nfor other artists and for release ourselves via Casa-D.\"\n","linknr":198,"url":"Markus_Dravs","recorded":1374763449,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Markus_Dravs&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Markus_Dravs&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vec